gomodel:SYNGO_4828  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Besides associating with actin cytoskeleton, protein 4.1N (EPB41L1) binds specifically to the membrane proximal region (MPR) of GluR1 but not GluR2 (PMID:12574408, PMID:11050113).\n\nFigure 3,4: Protein 4.1N (EPB41L1) is required for activity dependent GluR1 (GluA1/GRIA1) insertion.\n\nFigure 6: de-palmitoylation of the C811 residue facilitates phosphorylation within GluR1 MPR by PKC, which in turn enhances the interaction between 4.1N and GluR1.\n\nFigure 7,8: siRNA knockdown of protein 4.1N reduced expression levels of endogenous GluR1 containing AMPARs. Furthermore, 4.1N is required for LTP expression in acute hippocampal slices of adult mice.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Hippocampal neurons from embryonic day 18 (E18) rats\". \"Acute hippocampal slices were prepared 1 week after virus injection. Mice were anesthetized with intraperitoneal injection of avertin\".\n\nwe annotate against mouse species (intact tissue assays), but this paper has evidence for both species." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4828" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

